    "narrative": "For our April 22nd slate, **Will Smith** (72.68) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.80) lead the charge as our most formidable offensive options. **Will Smith** benefits from a potent combination of a 4.62 xERA opposing starter and favorable wind conditions that bolster his power floor. Meanwhile, **Tyler Freeman** is a high-upside play; the combination of a massive 14% park boost and the expectation of increased stolen base opportunities against a pitcher with a slow delivery makes him an elite start despite the middle-of-the-order assignment. **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez** also warrant specific mention as top-tier plays (67.52 and 66.93, respectively), as both capitalize on the significant platoon edge against a weak starter in a favorable park environment.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was leaving **Luis Arraez** (46.87) on the bench. While his profile is usually a staple of our lineup, he is stifled by a difficult matchup against Ohtani, whose 2.67 xERA creates a massive drag on offensive efficiency. Compared to the dynamic platoon edges enjoyed by **Gavin Sheets** or the tactical slotting of **Jeremiah Jackson**, the mathematical optimizer favored raw power and platoon advantages over the high-floor, low-ceiling approach **Luis Arraez** offers against an elite arm. We are also monitoring the risk associated with **Geraldo Perdomo** and **Matt Chapman**; both face daunting pitching matchups that pull their scores under 50.0. While they are currently active, their utility is marginal today, and we will be watching for defensive replacements or potential game-cap preservation needs if they struggle early against elite velocity.",
